This paper deals with privacy concerns in location-based services, which is a topic related to security and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of private information retrieval techniques, which are commonly used in database systems (cs.DB). The authors also mention the use of machine learning techniques to improve the privacy of their approach, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with shortest path computation, which is a topic related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper mentions experiments on real, large-scale road networks, which falls under the category of computer engineering (cs.CE).
